The population of the Earth is about 8 billion people.
The average human life expectancy is about 73 years.
The highest temperature ever recorded on Earth was 134¬∞F (56.7¬∞C) in Death Valley, California.
The lowest temperature ever recorded on Earth was -128.6¬∞F (-89.2¬∞C) in Antarctica.
The largest ocean on Earth is the Pacific Ocean.
The smallest continent on Earth is Australia.
The largest country by land area is Russia.
The smallest country by land area is Vatican City.
The most populous country in the world is India.
The official languages of the United Nations are Arabic, Chinese, English, French, Russian, and Spanish.
The currency of the European Union is the euro.
The International Space Station orbits the Earth every 90 minutes.
The first woman in space was Valentina Tereshkova.
The first African American woman in space was Mae Jemison.
The first person to walk in space was Alexei Leonov.
The Hubble Space Telescope has been orbiting Earth since 1990.
The James Webb Space Telescope was launched in 2021.
The Voyager 1 spacecraft is the farthest human-made object from Earth.
The speed of sound in air is about 767 miles per hour.
The Richter scale measures the magnitude of earthquakes.
The Fujita scale measures the intensity of tornadoes.
The Saffir-Simpson scale measures the intensity of hurricanes.
The Beaufort scale measures wind speed.
The pH scale measures the acidity or alkalinity of a solution.
The Kelvin scale is an absolute temperature scale.
The Celsius scale is a metric temperature scale.
The periodic table organizes the chemical elements.
DNA is the molecule that carries genetic information.
RNA is a molecule that plays a key role in protein synthesis.
Cells are the basic building blocks of all living organisms.
Photosynthesis is the process by which plants convert sunlight into energy.
Respiration is the process by which organisms release energy from food.
Evolution is the process of change in all forms of life over generations.
Natural selection is the mechanism by which evolution occurs.
The theory of relativity was developed by Albert Einstein.
Quantum mechanics is the study of the behavior of matter and energy at the atomic and subatomic level.
The Big Bang theory is the prevailing cosmological model for the universe.
The theory of plate tectonics explains the movement of Earth's continents.
The greenhouse effect is the warming of Earth's surface and atmosphere caused by greenhouse gases.
Climate change is the long-term alteration of temperature and typical weather patterns in a place.
Biodiversity is the variety of life on Earth.
Ecosystems are communities of living organisms and their physical environment.
Sustainability is the ability to meet the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.
Renewable energy is energy that is collected from renewable resources, which are naturally replenished on a human timescale.
Artificial intelligence is the simulation of human intelligence processes by machines.
Machine learning is a type of artificial intelligence that allows software applications to become more accurate in predicting outcomes without being explicitly programmed to do so.
Deep learning is a subfield of machine learning that uses artificial neural networks with multiple layers to extract higher-level features from raw input data.

The Internet of Things (IoT) is the network of physical objects embedded with sensors, software, and other technologies for the purpose of connecting and exchanging data with other devices and systems over the internet.
Blockchain is a distributed ledger technology that allows for secure and transparent transactions.
Cloud computing is the on-demand availability of computer system resources, especially data storage and computing power, without direct active management by the user.

Big data is a field that treats ways to analyze, systematically extract information from, or otherwise deal with data sets that are too large or complex to be dealt with by traditional data-processing application software.
